    "text": "comprehensive guide and checklist for aging-in-place renovations, exterior/interior accessibility modifications, and multi-story home planning in Oakland County, MI.\n\nUnderstanding Aging-in-Place Checklist & Guide | AAA Handyman Services\nCall Now!\n(248) 385-3432\nChecklist & Guide\nUnderstanding Aging-In-Place\nOlder adults are staying in their homes for as long as they can, and adults of all age groups are planning new construction and remodeling projects to factor in physical limitations.\nFree Printable Assessment Kit\nWant a Clean, Printable Checklist?\nEnter your email below to receive a beautifully formatted, printer-friendly version of this complete assessment checklist. It's designed to let you walk through your parents' or your own home with a clipboard and easily check off each item!\nYour Name\nYour Email\nGet Checklist & Print\nThank you!\nYour assessment kit is ready. If the print dialog does not open automatically, use the button below.\nPrint Assessment Kit\nAn Overview & Checklist\nThese aging-in-place renovations can range from providing better hallway lighting to adding a full bathroom to the first floor.\nThe checklist below contains features you may want to consider for your next new construction or renovation project. It also provides a quick reference for various aging-in-place issues. Because this list is not comprehensive, it’s best to also consult with a Certified Aging-in-Place specialist.\nHandyman vs. General Contractor: Setting Expectations\nTo set perfect expectations, we want to clarify exactly what our team handles:\nWhile we don't build elevator shafts, construct new additions, or perform major structural framing\n, we specialize in the essential accessibility retrofits that secure your home. We can install heavy-duty grab bars, change out your round door knobs for comfortable lever handles, secure your stair handrails, mount task lighting, and make minor threshold adjustments. Our services are perfectly tailored to"
  },
